50|$|H2SO5 is {{sometimes}} confused with <b>H2S2O8,</b> known as peroxydisulfuric acid. The disulfuric acid, {{which appears to}} be more widely used as its alkali metal salts, has the structure HO-S(O)2-O-O-S(O)2-OH.|$|E
5000|$|Peroxydisulfuric acid is the {{inorganic}} compound with the chemical formula <b>H2S2O8.</b> Also called Marshall's acid, it is sulfur oxoacid. [...] In structural terms {{it can be}} written HO3SOOSO3H. It contains sulfur in its +6 oxidation state and a peroxide group. Its salts, commonly known as persulfates, are industrially important as powerful oxidizing agents.|$|E

